i18n Phase 1: locale routing + UI chrome for 9 languages

Adds next-intl-backed locale routing so URLs like /th, /cn, /ja, /ko,
/ru, /fr, /es, /ar serve localised UI chrome alongside the default
English experience at /. Page bodies remain in English for now — full
content translation is Phase 2/3.

Infrastructure
- i18n/{routing,request,navigation}.ts: locale list, request-scoped
  message loader, locale-aware Link/useRouter wrappers
- messages/{en,th,cn,ja,ko,ru,fr,es,ar}.json: nav, action, footer, and
  language-switcher strings
- middleware.ts: composes maintenance gate + next-intl middleware,
  bypasses /admin and /api
- next.config.ts: wires createNextIntlPlugin, removes the legacy /th -> /
  redirect that now collides with the real Thai locale
- app/[locale]/layout.tsx: sets request locale, hydrates
  NextIntlClientProvider, generates static params for every locale
- components/i18n/HtmlLangSync.tsx: syncs <html lang/dir> with the
  active locale (incl. RTL for Arabic)

User-facing
- components/i18n/LanguageSwitcher.tsx: flag + native-name dropdown,
  desktop pill / compact mobile variants, ESC + outside-click close
- components/i18n/LocaleSuggestionBanner.tsx: "We noticed you speak X.
  Switch to <native>?" prompt driven by navigator.languages with a
  permanent localStorage dismissal flag
- components/layout/Header.tsx: translated nav labels + Reserve CTA,
  language switcher in desktop header and inside mobile drawer
- Bulk-swapped next/link -> @/i18n/navigation across all (public)
  pages and shared home/layout/checkout/seo components so internal
  navigation preserves the active locale prefix

Routes moved
- app/(public)/ -> app/[locale]/(public)/ (git rename, history preserved)
